text.__SUMMARY__: Shorea tenuiramulosa is a species of plant in the Dipterocarpaceae family. It is a tree endemic to Borneo.
text.Sources: Ashton, P. (1998). "Shorea tenuiramulosa". The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species. IUCN. 1998: e.T33436A9784275. doi:10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T33436A9784275.en. Retrieved 15 January 2018.
